OverHistory.NewCommentry: Umran Malik to Jos Buttler Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Umran Malik bowling to Jos Buttler, short of good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Jos Buttler plays an aggressive off drive on the front foot WICKET Jos Buttler c Nicholas Pooran b Umran Malik (Rajasthan Royals 75 Runs for 2 wickets), Appeal from the fielding sidetowards Wicket Keeper

Short of good length, outside off stump, bowled at 148 clicks and Buttler is beaten by the pace. There is a big appeal from all the Sunriser's players but the umpire is unmoved and they take it upstairs, UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball paces the bat and Buttler has to depart. Great use of the review this by Sunrisers!

OverHistory.UPDCommentry: T Natarajan to Shimron Hetmyer, 4 run(s), Hetmyer starts the last over with a boundary! Full length, off stump, Hetmyer pre-meditates the length and makes room for the scoop, gets it over the keeper's head for four.

OverHistory.NewCommentry: T Natarajan to Shimron Hetmyer Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: T Natarajan bowling to Shimron Hetmyer, yorker ball, pitching on off stump, Shimron Hetmyer plays an aggressive lofted on drive on the front foot WICKET Shimron Hetmyer b T Natarajan (Rajasthan Royals 207 Runs for 5 wickets)
OverHistory.UPDCommentry: T Natarajan to Shimron Hetmyer, WICKET Shimron Hetmyer b T Natarajan (Rajasthan Royals 207 Runs for 5 wickets). Natarajan strikes back and a powerful innings from Hetmyer comes to an end! Nails the yorker this time, Hetmyer misses on the slog shot and the stumps are castled!

OverHistory.NewCommentry: T Natarajan to Riyan Parag Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: T Natarajan bowling to Riyan Parag, good length ball, pitching outside leg stump, Riyan Parag leg glances it WICKET Riyan Parag c Nicholas Pooran b T Natarajan (Rajasthan Royals 210 Runs for 6 wickets)
OverHistory.UPDCommentry: T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, WICKET Riyan Parag c Nicholas Pooran b T Natarajan (Rajasthan Royals 210 Runs for 6 wickets). Good length, down the legs, Parag looks to flick this but gets an edge to Pooran behind the stumps and Rajasthan end the innings on 210/6 after 20 overs. Stay tuned for the chase!
This is the second-highest total at the venue! Can Rajasthan become the first team to defend a total this season?
